author: sussman
msg: Locking branch:  fix segfault in 'svnadmin lslocks'.

lock->comment to svn_cstring_count_newlines().

author: sussman
msg: Locking branch:  support RFC2518bis's idea of locking nonexistent resources.
Specifically, have mod_dav_svn treat 'LOCK nonexistentURL' as a
0-byte file PUT, but only if (1) the request came from a non-svn
client, and (2) autoversioning is turned on.
* subversion/mod_dav_svn/version.c
(dav_svn_attach_auto_revprops):   new factorized semi-public func.
(set_auto_revprops):   call factorized func.
* subversion/mod_dav_svn/dav_svn.h
(dav_svn_attach_auto_revprops):  declare semi-public func.
* subversion/mod_dav_svn/lock.c
(dav_svn_append_locks): create a 0-byte file via autoversioning commit.
Use the newly declared func to set revprops.
